    Full job description

    Job Title: Infrastructure Site Reliability Engineer (SRE)
    Location: Birmingham, AL
    Department: Technology
    Employment Type: Full Time - In-Office
    Reports To: CTO
    Compensation Range: $70,000-$100,000

    About the Role

    Were looking for a Site Reliability Engineer (SRE) to join our Infrastructure team at Linq. Youll be responsible for keeping our systems highly available, scalable, and fast while driving innovative approaches to reliability and redundancy.

    If you thrive in infrastructure, networking, and ops - and love building solutions that stop problems before they start - this role is for you.

    This is an in-office role in Birmingham, AL.

    Responsibilities

    • Automate data center and cloud infrastructure
    • Build redundancy and high-availability into every layer
    • Monitor and resolve issues before they impact users
    • Manage networks: routing, load balancing, firewalls, failover
    • Document playbooks and keep systems ready for disaster recovery

    What Were Looking For

    • 3+ years in infra, networking, or SRE roles
    • Experience with data centers, redundancy, and hybrid/cloud setups
    • Skilled in automation and configuration management (AWS, VPNs)
    • Familiar with monitoring tools (Prometheus/Grafana)
    • Solid grasp of network protocols and high-availability systems
    • Knowledge of scaling and replicating databases
    • Ability to document and communicate clearly and thoroughly
    • Strong troubleshooting skills and a proactive mindset

    Nice to Haves

    • Experience across multiple cloud platforms
    • Familiarity with automated build/test/release pipelines
    • Approaches to smooth, zero-downtime deployments
    • Exposure to security best practices and access controls
    • Ability to script or code (Python, Go, or Bash)
    • Background supporting always-on systems and on-call work
    • Practice with disaster recovery and continuity planning

    Why Join Linq?

    • Health, dental, and vision insurance.
    • Generous PTO
    • Collaborative team culture with room for growth and learning.
    • Opportunity to shape our brand and digital presence in a fast-growing company.
    • Work with a talented, collaborative, and ambitious team that will help you grow your skills in an exciting and fast-paced environment.

    Job Type: Full-time

    Pay: $70,000.00 - $100,000.00 per year

    Benefits:

    • 401(k)
    • Dental insurance
    • Health insurance
    • Paid time off
    • Vision insurance

    Application Question(s):

    • Why are you a good fit for this role?
    • How soon can you start?

    Location:

    • Birmingham, AL 35203 (Preferred)

    Work Location: In person
